Analyzed 103,024 ride bookings to gain insights into booking trends and overall business performance.

Found that the majority of rides were completed successfully, with an overall cancellation rate of 28.08%.

Identified the key reasons behind customer and driver cancellations, helping highlight areas that require operational improvements.

Observed that Cash and UPI were the most commonly used payment methods, showing a clear customer preference.

Prime Sedan contributed the highest booking value, while E-Bike recorded the highest average ride distance among all vehicle types.

Customer and driver ratings remained around 4.0, indicating a consistently good service experience across different ride categories.

Developed an interactive Power BI dashboard to visualize bookings, revenue, cancellations, vehicle performance, and customer ratings in a single view.

The insights from this project can help the business make data-driven decisions, improve customer satisfaction, reduce cancellations, and enhance overall operational efficiency.
